        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 4. Ventral view of right hyoid arch of Centromochlus akwe (A), UNT 10879, paratype, 47.5 mm SL. Abbreviations: ach, anterior ceratohyal; bra, branchiostegal rays; dhy, dorsal hypohyal; ihy, interhyal; pch, posterior ceratohyal; vhy, ventral hypohyal; uhy, urohyal. Branchial arches in dorsal view of Centromochlus akwe (B), UNT 10879, paratype, 47.5 mm SL. Abbreviations: abc, anterior basibranchial cartilage; bbr2, basibranchial 2; bbr3, basibranchial 3; cbr1-5, ceratobranchials 1 to 5 (anterior to posterior); ebr1-4, epibranchials 1 to 4 (anterior to posterior); hbr1, hypobranchial 1; hbr2, hypobranchial 2; hbr3, hypobranchial 3; pbr3, pharyngobranchial 3; pbr4, pharyngobranchial 4. Scale bar = 2 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4643572/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4643578>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 7. Anal fin in lateral view of Centromochlus akwe: (A) immature specimen, UNT 17391, 26.4 mm SL; (B) female, UNT 17391 37.7 mm SL and (C) mature male, MNRJ 51961 (h) 61.0 mm SL. Abbreviations: B1, first anal-fin branched ray; B10, tenth anal-fin branched ray; DD, deferent duct; u1-3, first and third anal-fin unbranched rays. Scale bar = 2 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4643578/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4643562>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 1. Centromochlus akwe, in dorsal (A), lateral (B) and ventral (C) views; MNRJ 51961 (holotype), 61.0 mm SL; adult male, showing modified anal fin. Brazil, Tocantins, Javaés River." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4643562/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4643568>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 2. Neurocranium of Centromochlus akwe, UNT 10879, paratype, 47.5 mm SL. Dorsal view. Abbreviations: Dfs, dorsal-fin spine; Dsp, dorsal-fin spineletspinelet; Epo, epiotic; Epop, epiotic process; Fro, frontal; Io1, first infraorbital; Le, lateral ethmoid; Mes, mesethmoid; Nas, nasal; Np2, middle nuchal plate; Np3, posterior nuchal plate; Pto, pterotic; Scl, posttemporal-supracleitrum; Soc, parietal-supraoccipital; Sop, suprapreopercle; Sph, sphenotic. Scale bar = 2 mm." ;
